http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/It%E2%80%99s-user-friendly/article13978066.ece

The Mysuru Zilla Panchayat’s mobile Android app will provide information on development works and various government schemes.Called ‘Mysuru’, the app gives information on how to avail oneself of different schemes, the progress of public works undertaken, and details on the government schemes launched under various departments.People can lodge complaints against officials or departments in the event of failure in providing legitimate service to beneficiaries. Complaints on substandard work can be registered along with a photograph of the work. Farmers can get information on scientific cultivation, tips to tackle crop diseases, and crop prices.Mysuru Zilla Panchayat president Puspavathi Amarnath said the user-friendly app would help reach out to people in remote places. The app can be downloaded onwww.mysuru.nic.in